                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363 Barco/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Piles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-05T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1928—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Your 25, April 2, 5 p.m. Department is informed the company is arranging to
                    have Stabler proceed to Bogotá as soon as possible. In the meantime the company
                    hopes that negotiations looking to a settlement of the controversy may be
                    initiated and be well on the way to successful conclusion by the time Stabler
                    arrives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
